    "description": "Gentamicin, approved in 1963, is an aminoglycoside that is active against a wide range of gram-negative bacteria, and usually provides synergistic killing vs. certain gram-positive cocci. Naturally produced by Micromonospora purpurea, a soil actinomycete. No activity against anaerobes, poor activity in a low pH environment. Not considered a reliable choice for P. aeruginosa.",
